    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>North American architectural style inspired by Victorian style, but made simpler and more plain. Although relatively plain in contrast to Victorian styles, the buildings are embellished with decorative trim. The floorplans are more regular than in Victorian homes. Flourished between 1870 and 1910, though isolated examples continued to be built well into the 1930s.</Note_Text>
